1
00:00:36,467 --> 00:00:39,033
<i> It's starting to feel heavy.</i>

2
00:00:39,167 --> 00:00:40,400
<i> And I'm getting sleepy.</i>

3
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:41,367
<i> But I just woke up.</i>

4
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,900
<i>That's just the
medicine's effect.</i>

5
00:00:43,033 --> 00:00:44,800
<i> I still can't reach Jessica.</i>

6
00:00:44,933 --> 00:00:48,433
<i>Speaking of Hazel,
have you tried calling her?</i>

7
00:00:48,567 --> 00:00:49,767
<i> He's here.</i>

8
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:50,633
<i> Look.</i>

9
00:00:50,767 --> 00:00:52,167
<i> Have mercy on Manuel.</i>

10
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:53,600
<i>Should I take him back
to the hospital</i>

11
00:00:53,733 --> 00:00:56,533
<i>so you and your illegitimate
kids can visit him again?</i>

12
00:00:56,667 --> 00:00:58,800
<i> You'll never see Manuel again.</i>

13
00:00:58,933 --> 00:00:59,967
<i> Manuel!</i>

14
00:01:00,100 --> 00:01:01,767
<i> You're a monster, Hazel!</i>

15
00:01:04,467 --> 00:01:06,633
<i> Are you looking for this?</i>

16
00:01:06,800 --> 00:01:07,367
<i> Mom.</i>

17
00:01:09,533 --> 00:01:11,467
<i>- Mom.
- Who are you going to call?</i>

18
00:01:11,600 --> 00:01:12,133
<i>- Who are you going to call?
- Mom!</i>

19
00:01:12,267 --> 00:01:13,067
<i> Is it Felma?</i>

20
00:01:14,467 --> 00:01:15,667
- Mommy.
- Who are you going to call?

21
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,100
- Mommy, please!
- Tell me!

22
00:01:18,967 --> 00:01:21,067
Mom! Mom!

23
00:01:21,200 --> 00:01:21,900
Mom, no!

24
00:01:22,033 --> 00:01:22,967
You want it? Then eat it!

25
00:01:23,100 --> 00:01:24,000
No!

26
00:01:24,133 --> 00:01:25,167
- No!
- Eat it!

27
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:27,400
- Eat it!
- Mom!

28
00:01:27,533 --> 00:01:28,500
Please stop!

29
00:01:28,633 --> 00:01:30,900
I'm not going to call
Aunt Felma!

30
00:01:31,033 --> 00:01:32,300
No!

31
00:01:32,433 --> 00:01:33,600
No.

32
00:01:33,733 --> 00:01:36,400
I'm not going to
call Aunt Felma, Mom.

33
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:43,867
Then who are you going to call?

34
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,633
I'll call the hospital
so they can pick Dad up!

35
00:01:47,767 --> 00:01:48,900
What?

36
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:49,967
Yes, Mom.

37
00:01:50,100 --> 00:01:52,667
Because you're putting
Dad's life in danger!

38
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:55,267
I thought you would
take care of him?

39
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:57,267
I can hear what's
happening upstairs.

40
00:01:57,400 --> 00:01:58,800
You're stressing him out.

41
00:01:58,933 --> 00:02:00,567
Why did you bring him here

42
00:02:00,700 --> 00:02:03,000
if you couldn't
take care of him?

43
00:02:03,133 --> 00:02:04,900
I've been taking care
of patients

44
00:02:05,033 --> 00:02:07,167
for more than two decades.

45
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:09,100
I know what I'm doing.

46
00:02:09,233 --> 00:02:11,433
Are you doubting my skills?

47
00:02:11,567 --> 00:02:13,367
He's not just your patient.

48
00:02:13,500 --> 00:02:15,267
He's your husband.

49
00:02:15,433 --> 00:02:18,267
Mom, he's suffering,
and you're causing it.

50
00:02:18,400 --> 00:02:19,500
What are you talking about?

51
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:23,833
Were you in the room?

52
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:26,867
Did you know what
really happened?

53
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:29,100
It's not me.

54
00:02:29,233 --> 00:02:32,133
Felma's causing him stress.

55
00:02:32,267 --> 00:02:34,133
He's trying to call that woman.

56
00:02:35,967 --> 00:02:36,767
Jessica...

57
00:02:37,967 --> 00:02:39,300
I'm doing my best here.

58
00:02:41,733 --> 00:02:45,367
I'm doing my best to make
things work with your dad,

59
00:02:45,500 --> 00:02:48,033
so our family can
be whole again.

60
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:49,200
So please.

61
00:02:50,967 --> 00:02:52,400
Will you please cooperate?

62
00:02:59,333 --> 00:03:00,433
One chance.

63
00:03:02,767 --> 00:03:03,800
Just one chance.

64
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:06,733
That's all I'm asking.

65
00:03:10,067 --> 00:03:11,367
Please give me a chance.

66
00:03:13,067 --> 00:03:15,633
I just want to prove myself.

67
00:03:15,767 --> 00:03:16,767
Just one chance.

68
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:21,167
One chance, please?

69
00:03:28,900 --> 00:03:32,233
Miss Andrea, whatever I
told you over the phone

70
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:37,233
when we talked, that's exactly
what I'll say again now.

71
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:40,933
I really don't know
where Manuel is.

72
00:03:41,067 --> 00:03:43,300
Miss Cruz, okay.

73
00:03:43,433 --> 00:03:45,900
I'm being honest
with you here, okay?

74
00:03:46,033 --> 00:03:49,167
I really don't know
where your dad is.

75
00:03:49,300 --> 00:03:53,133
In fact, ever since Hazel
resigned,

76
00:03:53,267 --> 00:03:54,033
we've lost touch.

77
00:03:54,200 --> 00:03:55,700
We haven't spoken since.

78
00:03:56,800 --> 00:04:01,000
Does no one here really
know where they are?

79
00:04:03,333 --> 00:04:06,433
I'm not sure if he mentioned
anything to Nurse Alice.

80
00:04:07,767 --> 00:04:11,067
We just want to know
how he's doing.

81
00:04:12,533 --> 00:04:14,667
We haven't heard
anything about him.

82
00:04:15,933 --> 00:04:18,067
I feel your pain.

83
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,200
But I really don't know.

84
00:04:19,333 --> 00:04:21,233
I really don't know
what else to tell you.

85
00:04:21,367 --> 00:04:23,433
I honestly have no idea.

86
00:04:23,567 --> 00:04:27,233
To be honest, I even volunteered
to visit Manuel myself.

87
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:29,167
But Hazel refused.

88
00:04:32,700 --> 00:04:34,533
What is she doing here?

89
00:04:38,933 --> 00:04:44,133
Alice, maybe you know
where Hazel and Dad are.

90
00:04:44,267 --> 00:04:45,733
Just tell me.

91
00:04:47,567 --> 00:04:48,733
Get on your knees first.

92
00:04:48,867 --> 00:04:49,800
Alice!

93
00:04:53,667 --> 00:04:54,800
Wait, wait.

94
00:04:54,933 --> 00:04:56,033
No, don't do that.

95
00:04:56,167 --> 00:04:57,600
It was a joke.

96
00:04:57,733 --> 00:04:58,633
A joke?

97
00:04:58,767 --> 00:05:01,067
That was a bad one!

98
00:05:01,233 --> 00:05:03,733
Sorry, Nurse Miles.

99
00:05:03,867 --> 00:05:04,800
Sorry, Andrea.

100
00:05:06,167 --> 00:05:07,933
I really don't know either.

101
00:05:08,067 --> 00:05:11,500
Hazel said she wants to be safe.

102
00:05:11,633 --> 00:05:13,767
That's why she
didn't tell anyone.

103
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:14,567
That's it.

104
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:54,333
You're totally crazy!

105
00:05:54,467 --> 00:05:55,900
Why? Am I that bad?

106
00:05:56,033 --> 00:05:57,100
I'm catching your wickedness.

107
00:05:57,233 --> 00:05:58,933
Well, I like it.

108
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:02,467
You should've made her kneel
before you took it back.

109
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:05,067
Then I'd be in
trouble with Miles.

110
00:06:05,200 --> 00:06:06,500
Miles can't do anything.

111
00:06:06,633 --> 00:06:07,933
She'll give you nothing
but a verbal warning.

112
00:06:09,700 --> 00:06:12,133
But seriously, friend.

113
00:06:12,267 --> 00:06:14,467
How are you getting
by these days?

114
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:19,233
Let's just say I used
my acting skills

115
00:06:19,367 --> 00:06:23,100
to manipulate the Wilsons.

116
00:06:23,233 --> 00:06:27,900
You know, I forced them to
send a monthly allowance.

117
00:06:28,033 --> 00:06:29,000
Wow.

118
00:06:29,133 --> 00:06:30,367
How?

119
00:06:30,500 --> 00:06:31,967
I guilt-tripped them.

120
00:06:32,100 --> 00:06:33,767
I played the drama.

121
00:06:33,900 --> 00:06:36,133
Of course, I told them,
if it weren't for them,

122
00:06:36,267 --> 00:06:38,267
Manuel wouldn't be paralyzed.

123
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,633
Then you know what I did?

124
00:06:39,767 --> 00:06:41,467
I filmed Manuel in the ICU.

125
00:06:41,633 --> 00:06:44,133
The couple felt
so sorry for him.

126
00:06:44,267 --> 00:06:46,867
They even doubled the
money we agreed on!

127
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:48,200
I'm so good, right?

128
00:06:48,333 --> 00:06:49,800
You're amazing, friend!

129
00:06:49,933 --> 00:06:51,433
You're embarrassing, Mom.

130
00:06:56,967 --> 00:06:58,167
What did you say?

131
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:05,533
You heard me.

132
00:07:09,533 --> 00:07:12,133
You heard me, Mom.

133
00:07:12,267 --> 00:07:14,867
Jessica, stop talking
back to your mom.

134
00:07:15,033 --> 00:07:18,100
But what she did
was wrong, Auntie.

135
00:07:18,233 --> 00:07:20,067
Aren't you ashamed, Mommy?

136
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:22,433
You're scamming
an elderly couple.

137
00:07:22,567 --> 00:07:24,633
What's so shameful
about what I did?

138
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:27,533
What scam are you talking about?

139
00:07:27,667 --> 00:07:29,400
They owe us a lot of money.

140
00:07:29,533 --> 00:07:32,367
If it weren't for them,
your dad wouldn't be paralyzed.

141
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:35,533
But that's no excuse
to take their money.

142
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:37,867
And now you're even using Dad?

143
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:39,233
That's so low of you, Mom.

144
00:07:40,967 --> 00:07:41,600
Wait.

145
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,100
- What now?
- Hazel!

146
00:07:47,233 --> 00:07:47,633
Hazel!

147
00:07:47,800 --> 00:07:48,767
You're so rude!

148
00:07:48,900 --> 00:07:51,600
- You're embarrassing me!
- Hazel, enough!

149
00:07:51,733 --> 00:07:53,367
- You're embarrassing me!
- Hazel!

150
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:54,567
- What now?
- Hazel, enough!

151
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:55,833
Hey!

152
00:07:55,967 --> 00:07:57,833
You're getting used to
hurting your own child!

153
00:07:57,967 --> 00:08:00,233
She's also getting used
to talking back to me!

154
00:08:00,367 --> 00:08:02,067
Ever since she moved in
at Felma's house,

155
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,067
she's been rebellious.

156
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:04,500
What? Do you want me
to break your horns?

157
00:08:04,633 --> 00:08:05,633
Friend!

158
00:08:05,767 --> 00:08:07,800
Come on! That's enough!

159
00:08:07,933 --> 00:08:09,533
I'll take care of my godchild!

160
00:08:09,667 --> 00:08:10,533
Go on!

161
00:08:13,400 --> 00:08:14,567
Talk to her.

162
00:08:25,067 --> 00:08:26,900
Come on, Jessica.

163
00:08:27,033 --> 00:08:29,567
Don't make your mom angry
anymore.

164
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:34,833
Auntie, please help me
and Dad get out of here.

165
00:08:36,733 --> 00:08:38,500
I'm sorry, godchild.

166
00:08:38,633 --> 00:08:41,233
But I can't do that.

167
00:08:41,367 --> 00:08:43,867
I have to confess
something to you.

168
00:08:44,000 --> 00:08:49,933
Your mom is my best friend,
but I'm afraid of her.

169
00:08:50,067 --> 00:08:52,533
Why?

170
00:08:52,667 --> 00:08:54,433
I don't want to talk about it.

171
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:58,533
Your mom is a good friend.

172
00:08:58,667 --> 00:09:01,567
But a terrible enemy.

173
00:09:01,700 --> 00:09:06,467
She's capable of doing
things you'd never imagine.

174
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,167
So just follow her.

175
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:09,267
Trust me.

176
00:09:09,400 --> 00:09:11,300
She's a terrifying enemy.

177
00:09:12,900 --> 00:09:18,233
<i>If you want your Dad to survive
and see him get better, obey me.</i>

178
00:09:18,367 --> 00:09:20,233
<i> Or else...</i>

179
00:09:20,367 --> 00:09:22,067
<i>you'll regret it
for the rest of your life.</i>

180
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:43,000
Thank you very much,
Colonel Sarabia.

181
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:46,500
I hope you can refer us
right away.

182
00:09:46,633 --> 00:09:50,533
Additionally, we request
that the van be traced

183
00:09:50,667 --> 00:09:53,467
through the Manila Traffic
Authority Office.

184
00:09:53,600 --> 00:09:55,033
Yes, Sir. Thank you.

185
00:09:57,867 --> 00:09:59,500
What referral
are you talking about?

186
00:10:02,933 --> 00:10:04,533
A private investigator.

187
00:10:04,667 --> 00:10:06,400
I'm trying to find someone.

188
00:10:06,533 --> 00:10:09,467
Because we keep
hitting dead ends.

189
00:10:09,600 --> 00:10:11,200
What about the kids?

190
00:10:11,333 --> 00:10:15,167
Have they filed a
missing person report?

191
00:10:15,300 --> 00:10:16,700
Yes.

192
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:19,033
But still no news.

193
00:10:19,167 --> 00:10:22,967
Do you think posting on
social media would help?

194
00:10:23,100 --> 00:10:24,500
Why not?

195
00:10:24,633 --> 00:10:26,000
So more people can see.

196
00:10:28,133 --> 00:10:30,000
Please help me.

197
00:10:30,133 --> 00:10:31,600
Sure.

198
00:10:31,733 --> 00:10:35,100
I'll give a reward
of 100,000 pesos.

199
00:10:35,267 --> 00:10:36,833
100,000 pesos?

200
00:10:36,967 --> 00:10:38,700
Are you sure?

201
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:42,000
I'll pay even a million.

202
00:10:42,133 --> 00:10:45,467
As long as someone can
tell me where my kids' dad is.

203
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,033
Finish it, Dad, okay?

204
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:04,233
So you can get stronger.

205
00:11:04,367 --> 00:11:05,467
Do you want some water?

206
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:08,800
Or should I make you juice, Dad?

207
00:11:08,967 --> 00:11:10,133
Just water, dear.

208
00:11:10,267 --> 00:11:10,967
Okay.

209
00:11:14,833 --> 00:11:17,567
Jessica, could you
try calling Felma?

210
00:11:19,200 --> 00:11:22,433
She might be worried.

211
00:11:22,567 --> 00:11:23,867
Sorry, Dad.

212
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:26,233
There really isn't
any signal here.

213
00:11:28,133 --> 00:11:30,333
I need to go outside.

214
00:11:30,467 --> 00:11:32,633
It's pretty far.

215
00:11:32,767 --> 00:11:35,833
But don't worry,
they'll visit next week.

216
00:11:36,833 --> 00:11:37,900
Your mom said that?

217
00:11:42,167 --> 00:11:44,567
I was there when she
called Aunt Felma.

218
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:51,767
You mean Hazel's
telling the truth?

219
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:53,933
Yes, Dad.

220
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:56,100
Mom has changed.

221
00:11:56,233 --> 00:11:58,833
Did you know that even
when you're asleep,

222
00:11:58,967 --> 00:12:01,300
I catch her just looking at you?

223
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:05,833
Mom is so happy taking
care of you, Dad.

224
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:13,067
I even catch her talking
to you while you sleep.

225
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,800
She's always apologizing.

226
00:12:16,567 --> 00:12:18,300
So I'm thinking...

227
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,833
maybe we can be a family again?

228
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:29,900
Aren't you happy the three of us
are together?

229
00:12:37,700 --> 00:12:39,833
Of course when I'm with you...

230
00:12:41,800 --> 00:12:42,767
I'm really happy

231
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:44,567
No doubt about that.

232
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:49,133
But I'm even happier when
I'm with your Aunt Felma.

233
00:12:49,300 --> 00:12:55,667
Jeffrey, Coleen,
and of course...

234
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:59,933
hopefully your older
sister Andrea, too.

235
00:13:00,067 --> 00:13:05,300
Do you remember when
we all ate together?

236
00:13:05,433 --> 00:13:06,333
Son, that's enough.

237
00:13:06,467 --> 00:13:06,967
Last one, last one.

238
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:08,033
That's too much already.

239
00:13:08,567 --> 00:13:10,667
I might get spoiled.

240
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:14,600
Dad, thank you for saving me,

241
00:13:14,733 --> 00:13:16,100
even though you knew you could
get hurt.

242
00:13:18,000 --> 00:13:19,833
That was truly the most
delicious

243
00:13:19,967 --> 00:13:21,633
and happiest breakfast I've had

244
00:13:21,800 --> 00:13:24,000
since we came back
to the Philippines.

245
00:13:26,767 --> 00:13:31,000
Especially if your sister
Andrea had been there, right?

246
00:13:32,933 --> 00:13:34,933
If it happens, my family
will finally be whole.

247
00:13:37,667 --> 00:13:39,567
Don't you think...

248
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,767
that you, Mom, and I already
make a complete family?

249
00:13:46,100 --> 00:13:46,967
Sweetie...

250
00:13:50,567 --> 00:13:51,733
sorry, but...

251
00:13:53,933 --> 00:13:55,033
that's not really the case.

252
00:13:56,167 --> 00:13:59,000
They've made me feel like
they're my family,

253
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:06,100
your Aunt Felma, your siblings
Jeffrey, Andrea, Coleen...

254
00:14:07,767 --> 00:14:09,167
and of course, you.

255
00:14:10,967 --> 00:14:12,233
That's why...

256
00:14:13,100 --> 00:14:16,167
you know, I really want
to get better

257
00:14:16,300 --> 00:14:19,200
so I can finally take care
of the annulment with Hazel.

258
00:14:24,767 --> 00:14:26,067
No, Manuel.

259
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:29,933
There will be no annulment.

260
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:30,867
None.

261
00:14:43,400 --> 00:14:44,367
Mommy.

262
00:14:47,600 --> 00:14:48,467
Jessica.

263
00:14:50,000 --> 00:14:51,767
That's the Jessica I want.

264
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:54,167
Someone who listens.

265
00:14:54,300 --> 00:14:55,633
Someone who obeys.

266
00:14:57,633 --> 00:15:01,600
Thank you for building me up
with your dad.

267
00:15:03,067 --> 00:15:05,300
Mom, how long are
we staying here?

268
00:15:06,667 --> 00:15:09,733
How long are we hiding Dad?

269
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:15,033
Until your dad fully forgets
that Felma and her kids exist.

270
00:15:16,433 --> 00:15:17,833
Until the very end.

271
00:15:19,167 --> 00:15:21,400
Until we get our happy ending.

272
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:25,033
But what about Aunt Felma
and her children?

273
00:15:25,167 --> 00:15:26,867
What about them?

274
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:31,433
I mean, surely they won't stop
looking for Dad.

275
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:35,167
They won't see your dad.

276
00:15:37,167 --> 00:15:38,467
Unless...

277
00:15:41,533 --> 00:15:42,900
someone tells them.

278
00:15:46,233 --> 00:15:48,333
If they find out...

279
00:15:48,467 --> 00:15:49,667
where we are...

280
00:15:50,633 --> 00:15:52,400
it only means one thing.

281
00:15:54,533 --> 00:15:56,367
Someone betrayed me.

282
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,033
And that someone is you.

283
00:16:02,967 --> 00:16:05,533
Could you betray...

284
00:16:05,667 --> 00:16:07,400
your own mother?

285
00:16:15,033 --> 00:16:18,100
What's this link
your Aunt Alice forwarded?

286
00:16:22,633 --> 00:16:24,133
Oh, well.

287
00:16:24,267 --> 00:16:26,267
Good luck...

288
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,600
finding out where Manuel is.

289
00:16:36,433 --> 00:16:38,500
I've got this, Ma'am.

290
00:16:39,433 --> 00:16:41,367
I'll take care of it.
Come on, hurry.

291
00:16:41,500 --> 00:16:43,367
I have a surprise for you.

292
00:16:43,533 --> 00:16:46,200
You know what? I cooked.

293
00:16:50,233 --> 00:16:53,133
Welcome home, Andrea!

294
00:16:53,267 --> 00:16:55,667
From Didang!

295
00:16:58,067 --> 00:16:59,400
Dig in!

296
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:03,333
I feel like sulking now.

297
00:17:03,467 --> 00:17:07,900
Not a single one of you wants
to try what I cooked.

298
00:17:08,033 --> 00:17:09,833
It's not that, Didang.

299
00:17:12,233 --> 00:17:14,467
It's just that
today's been unlucky.

300
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,900
Why?

301
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:23,067
Colonel Sarabia took us
to the...

302
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,767
Manila Traffic Authority Office.

303
00:17:25,900 --> 00:17:27,833
He showed us...

304
00:17:27,967 --> 00:17:30,033
the CCTV footage

305
00:17:30,167 --> 00:17:32,067
where the van...

306
00:17:32,200 --> 00:17:35,767
Hazel used to take Manuel
out of the hospital was caught.

307
00:17:37,167 --> 00:17:38,000
Oh no.

308
00:17:38,133 --> 00:17:39,533
Bad news.

309
00:17:39,667 --> 00:17:41,000
Yes, Didang.

310
00:17:45,333 --> 00:17:49,000
You know, Hazel's accomplice
is a criminal.

311
00:17:49,167 --> 00:17:51,767
They know which streets
don't have CCTV.

312
00:17:51,900 --> 00:17:52,667
Can you believe it?

313
00:17:52,800 --> 00:17:53,567
From the hospital
onto the highway,

314
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:54,600
that's only where
they were caught.

315
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:57,500
Then they turned onto
a street and vanished.

316
00:17:57,633 --> 00:17:59,667
Will we even see Dad again?

317
00:17:59,800 --> 00:18:01,600
I wonder how he's doing.

318
00:18:01,733 --> 00:18:03,667
I'm so furious
at that evil Hazel.

319
00:18:03,800 --> 00:18:05,300
But hopefully...

320
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:09,033
Hopefully,
she's not neglecting Dad.

321
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:10,133
Jessica is there.

322
00:18:10,267 --> 00:18:12,333
I'm sure she won't let
anything happen to Dad.

323
00:18:14,100 --> 00:18:19,000
But what if Dad's condition
develops complications?

324
00:18:20,833 --> 00:18:22,467
No.

325
00:18:22,633 --> 00:18:23,867
No.

326
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:25,767
Let's not think
negatively.

327
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,367
Lord, please...

328
00:18:28,500 --> 00:18:31,133
please don't let anything
happen to Dad.

329
00:18:36,067 --> 00:18:36,967
A text just came in.

330
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:41,633
I know where Manuel Cruz is.

331
00:18:41,767 --> 00:18:42,500
What?

332
00:18:42,633 --> 00:18:43,533
What?

333
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:50,333
Hello?

334
00:18:51,667 --> 00:18:53,033
Yes, this is Jeffrey Cruz.

335
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,400
Are you sure you know
where my dad is?

336
00:18:57,367 --> 00:18:58,600
Yes.

337
00:18:59,633 --> 00:19:01,200
I helped bring him there.

338
00:19:01,333 --> 00:19:02,667
Where?

339
00:19:02,800 --> 00:19:04,467
Where did you take my dad?

340
00:19:04,600 --> 00:19:06,100
Meet me.

341
00:19:06,233 --> 00:19:08,267
I'll tell you there.

342
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,167
And bring the reward.

343
00:19:13,233 --> 00:19:14,633
Wait.

344
00:19:14,767 --> 00:19:16,200
How do we know
you're not a scammer?

345
00:19:16,333 --> 00:19:18,333
That you're not lying to us?

346
00:19:18,467 --> 00:19:20,033
Manuel Cruz is paraplegic.

347
00:19:20,167 --> 00:19:21,467
Is that enough?

348
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,400
When do we meet? Where?

349
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:26,300
Today.

350
00:19:26,433 --> 00:19:28,233
I'll text you the location.

351
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:40,633
Tom, Kenjie, thank you.

352
00:19:40,767 --> 00:19:42,500
Wait for me downstairs.

353
00:19:42,633 --> 00:19:44,033
We still need to talk.

354
00:20:07,100 --> 00:20:08,067
Thank you.

355
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:15,833
Son, has he replied yet?

356
00:20:15,967 --> 00:20:17,133
Not yet.

357
00:20:17,267 --> 00:20:20,000
I'll text him, Mom.
I'll text him again.

358
00:20:22,233 --> 00:20:23,967
Bro, we're already here.

359
00:20:24,100 --> 00:20:25,400
Are you on your way?

360
00:20:30,533 --> 00:20:31,867
I'll just wait for his reply.

361
00:20:59,767 --> 00:21:01,133
Hello, Miss H?

362
00:21:02,133 --> 00:21:04,867
I'll match their reward.

363
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:07,967
What reward?

364
00:21:08,100 --> 00:21:10,867
Don't play coy.

365
00:21:11,033 --> 00:21:14,033
I had Maximo tail you

366
00:21:14,167 --> 00:21:16,200
because I don't trust you.

367
00:21:16,333 --> 00:21:17,533
Okay.

368
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:19,367
But...

369
00:21:19,500 --> 00:21:21,233
what do we do about it, Miss H?

370
00:21:21,367 --> 00:21:23,800
You'll just match
the 100,000 pesos?

371
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:25,533
And what do you want?

372
00:21:25,667 --> 00:21:26,900
Should I double it?

373
00:21:27,033 --> 00:21:28,033
What are you?

374
00:21:28,167 --> 00:21:29,400
Don't be greedy.

375
00:21:29,533 --> 00:21:30,767
No.

376
00:21:30,900 --> 00:21:33,233
Just 150,000 pesos.

377
00:21:34,100 --> 00:21:37,133
I'm planning to charge them
200,000 pesos anyway.

378
00:21:37,267 --> 00:21:39,167
Seems like they're willing
to pay.

379
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:40,633
Oh, really?

380
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:43,900
Try it.

381
00:21:44,033 --> 00:21:45,533
So by tomorrow,

382
00:21:45,667 --> 00:21:47,300
everyone on social media
will know

383
00:21:47,433 --> 00:21:49,133
about your plate cloning
business.

384
00:21:50,733 --> 00:21:52,000
Did you forget?

385
00:21:52,133 --> 00:21:53,867
Maximo is loyal to me.

386
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:55,900
He's embarrassed
that he recommended you.

387
00:21:56,033 --> 00:21:58,200
Because it looks like
you'll betray me.

388
00:21:59,933 --> 00:22:01,433
What now?

389
00:22:01,567 --> 00:22:02,800
You're still pressing?

390
00:22:02,933 --> 00:22:04,333
No, no more.

391
00:22:04,467 --> 00:22:06,233
Just send the 100,000
pesos to my account.

392
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,533
- Mister.
- Yes, Ma'am?

393
00:22:25,767 --> 00:22:27,633
Can I get another coffee?

394
00:22:40,400 --> 00:22:42,100
Son, can you check?

395
00:22:42,233 --> 00:22:43,500
He might have already replied.

396
00:22:43,633 --> 00:22:44,933
Or try calling him.

397
00:22:45,067 --> 00:22:46,533
Okay, Mom. I'll call him.

398
00:22:52,367 --> 00:22:53,267
What happened?

399
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:56,533
Why?

400
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:05,733
Why, son?

401
00:23:05,867 --> 00:23:07,233
Mom, he blocked me.

402
00:23:08,800 --> 00:23:11,133
It feels like he's
messing with us.

403
00:23:11,267 --> 00:23:13,100
Son.

404
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:15,333
He seems legit.

405
00:23:15,467 --> 00:23:19,867
He even knows that your
dad is paraplegic.

406
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:20,633
Please give me the number.

407
00:23:20,767 --> 00:23:22,067
- I'll call him.
- Here you go.

408
00:23:27,133 --> 00:23:28,333
Thank you.

409
00:23:33,133 --> 00:23:34,400
I can't reach him either.

410
00:23:34,533 --> 00:23:35,867
I told you, Mom.

411
00:23:41,567 --> 00:23:43,300
This is so frustrating!

412
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:55,300
I'm sorry, Manuel.

413
00:23:57,133 --> 00:23:58,900
I've hurt you for so many years.

414
00:24:00,467 --> 00:24:02,233
Neglected you.

415
00:24:02,367 --> 00:24:04,833
But, thank you.

416
00:24:04,967 --> 00:24:07,533
Because of all those years
I neglected you,

417
00:24:09,333 --> 00:24:10,667
you endured me.

418
00:24:11,900 --> 00:24:12,867
You put up with me.

419
00:24:14,133 --> 00:24:16,133
That's why I'm sure

420
00:24:16,267 --> 00:24:18,767
I'll never meet
anyone like you again.

421
00:24:20,567 --> 00:24:22,433
So let me make it
up to you, okay?

422
00:24:23,767 --> 00:24:25,567
Let me take care of you.

423
00:24:34,633 --> 00:24:36,833
When are Felma and
the kids coming?

424
00:24:49,267 --> 00:24:51,400
Manuel, can't we...

425
00:24:52,633 --> 00:24:54,367
not talk about
them for now?

426
00:24:55,867 --> 00:24:58,867
Can't it just be us...

427
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:00,400
without them for a while?

428
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:04,633
Hazel, there's nothing
left to discuss.

429
00:25:06,100 --> 00:25:07,333
We're done.

430
00:25:07,467 --> 00:25:08,700
No.

431
00:25:08,833 --> 00:25:09,967
Manuel, not yet.

432
00:25:10,100 --> 00:25:11,367
We're not done.

433
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:13,767
For you, it's not over yet.
But for me, it's done.

434
00:25:15,600 --> 00:25:16,933
What do I have to do?

435
00:25:18,800 --> 00:25:21,333
So that even just a glance,

436
00:25:21,467 --> 00:25:22,900
even just a peek,

437
00:25:23,900 --> 00:25:26,000
you'll see me again?

438
00:25:26,133 --> 00:25:27,067
Sorry.

439
00:25:28,300 --> 00:25:30,100
But no matter
what changes you make,

440
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,667
I won't change my mind.

441
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:38,333
I'll go through
with the annulment.

442
00:25:51,033 --> 00:25:53,300
No! You can't!

443
00:25:53,433 --> 00:25:54,233
You have no rights!

444
00:25:54,367 --> 00:25:55,467
You're just a mistress!

445
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:57,900
Even if one of you
has to disappear,

446
00:25:58,033 --> 00:25:59,167
so you won't get back together,

447
00:25:59,300 --> 00:26:01,167
so you won't be together, fine!

448
00:26:01,300 --> 00:26:06,333
I'm scared of Mom.
I can't defy her.

449
00:26:06,467 --> 00:26:07,533
Hello, Uncle Abel?

450
00:26:07,667 --> 00:26:09,067
This is Jessica.

451
00:26:09,233 --> 00:26:10,767
Jessica?

452
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:12,467
Jessica!
